          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-LI7"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Quasimonoenergetic  neutrons were produced by",
                " protons impinging on Li-nat-target (92.5% of Li-7) via",
                " Li-7(p,n) reaction. 70 MeV proton beam from K=110 MeV",
                " AVF cyclotron of CYRIC. Thickness of Li plate was",
                "measured to be 4.74 mm (2 MeV energy loss for 70 MeV",
                "proton) using a micrometer with error less 0.05 mm.",
                "1 m collimator of copper and iron.",
                "Li target was surrounded by concrete and steel shield",
                "to reduce background."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron spectrum consists of full-energy peak due to",
                "Li-7(p,n)Be-7 reaction and smooth continuum component",
                "attributable to multi-body breakup process.",
                "TOF data were used for a part of continuum spectrum",
                "close to peak and lower energy part was estimated",
                "using formula of M.Baba+ (1999, see REL-REF).",
                "Neutron spectrum is shown on Fig.2 of J,ANE,36,2009.",
                "Total (peak+ continuum) flux 2.60E+6 n/cm**2/sec,",
                "peak neutron fluence 1.34E+6 n/cm**2/sec.",
                "Ratio of peak neutrons to total neutron yield in the",
                "spectrum was found about 0.48 ."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "1",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   Neutron spectrum was measured by TOF technique."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 2.5 hr irradiation."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Bi-Conc-Conc-Bi stacked samples were placed",
                "        250 cm from Li-target."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Induced nuclides activity was measured",
                "nondestructively using HPGe-gamma-ray spectroscopy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "1",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Organic liquid scintillation detector NE213 of",
                "14 cm diameter, 10 cm long, equipped with large dynamic",
                "range n-gamma discriminator. Placed at 7.65 m from",
                "Li-target.NE213 detection efficiency was obtained by",
                "SCINFUL-R Monte Carlo code (Meigo, 1997) with estimated",
                "error 10 %."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For gamma-ray counting of three times 2 h, 5 h,",
                "       10 h."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Bismuth plates (9 cm diameter, 1 cm thick) sandwiched",
                "ordinary concrete samples (5 cm diameter, 2 cm thick)",
                "as Bi-Conc-Conc-Bi.",
                "    Atom density of elements in ordinary concrete is:",
                "           (in n/cm**3 * 10**24 units)",
                "H  - 1.23E-2      Ca - 3.32E-4       K  -  4.41E-4",
                "O  - 4.38E-3      Si - 1.59E-2       C  -  1.10E-4",
                "Na - 9.22E-4      Al - 1.67E-3       Fe -  3.32E-4"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Activation of concrete by quasimonoenergetic neutrons",
                "was measured. Activation cross sections on bismuth",
                "was measured to confirm the experimental procedure.",
                " Reaction rates for formation radionuclides identified",
                "from the gamma-ray spectra and half-life were",
                "estimated. Decay data for the investigated nuclides",
                "were take from NUDAT2 : www.nndc.bnl.gov/nudat2 ."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Measured radioactivity  concentrations of nuclides",
                "induced in concrete (peak neutron fluence",
                "1.45E+9 n/cm**2C , peak neutron energy 64.5 MeV):",
                "Nuclide  Half-life    Reaction   Activity (Bq/g)",
                "Na-24    14.96 hr   Al-27(n,a)Na-24       6270+-107",
                "Na-22    2.6 hr     Al-27(n,2n+a)Na-22    66774+-3966",
                "                    Na-23(n,2n)Na-22",
                "Mn-52g   5.59 d     Mn-55(n,4n)Mn-52g     34+-15",
                "Mn-54    312.3 d    Mn-55(n,2n)Mn-54      18423+-1044",
                "                    Co-59(n,2t)Mn-54",
                "Co-56    77.27 d    Co-59(n,4n)Co-56      1293+-199"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " For the peak efficiency of HPGe-detector including",
                " self-absorption.",
                " For coincidence-sunning effect.",
                " For the beam current fluctuation during irradiation.",
                " For neutron beam attenuation by two processes-",
                "- measuring the neutron flux by monitor reactions",
                " Bi-209(n,4n), Bi-209(n,5n), Bi-209(n,7n) reported by",
                "E.Kim+ from both front and rear monitors (Bi-209) and",
                "- from total cross sections of Bi and concrete.",
                "Neutron attenuation along samples obtained from total",
                "cross-section was found about 37 % in the peak region."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
